  schema:name "large language model" ;
  schema:description "A **large language model** (LLM) is a neural network trained on large amounts of text to predict the next token in a sequence. By learning statistical patterns in language, LLMs acquire the ability to generate coherent text, follow instructions, answer questions, write code, and perform reasoning tasks." ;
